column1: 84019;instagram;2019-01-09 07:18:08;FALSE;"#metoo #人工流產 #面對傷痛才會痊癒
這是一篇文長而且非沉重的內容，首先感謝昨天在直播看我哭了很久的朋友們，一月對我來說真的太困難了；另外想請「極端的宗教朋友」、「道德魔人」、「酸民」們請先動動手退我的讚 / 追蹤，然後把頁面關閉，謝謝您。
這是我在2019年給自己的禮物，我不需要討拍、也不需要任何人的批評指教，我只是希望給自己的傷痛一個出口，同時也希望曾經和我經歷過類似事情的人，可以勇敢一些，身邊的朋友家人可以更正面積極的多陪伴一些，很多事真的不是一句沒關係、一個擁抱，就能讓傷痛不在了。
是的，我在14歲（2007）時曾遭到一位香港某大電視台（現在仍在）的蘇姓龍虎舞師 #性侵害。
他利用家人和孩子的信任，以學武術為由，要求14歲的我和我的一位女同學，在晚上去海邊做體能訓練，並要求我們不穿內衣，同時用手機播放18禁影片給我們看，最後以神鬼說的因由把我帶到海中的浮台附近，繼而性侵得逞。
我承認14歲的時候真的是智商欠缺，不然也不會相信這種言論，在發現正在發生什麼的時候，已經來不及了...事件過後我們當然再也沒有去學習過所謂的「武術」了，也因為我們拒絕學習，所以家人才會知道。
當時我爸說了一句「xx圈的人大不了就是上下其手，難不成你還給人家睡了」，為此我起碼恨了他6-8年，而當時身邊的朋友和同學卻是抱著懷疑態度拒絕相信有這樣的事情發生，甚至認為一個女生會為了討拍而捏造這種事，我為這些人的想法與思想感到可恥，其實我們需要的不是身邊的人去評價這件事，而是陪伴和告訴我們怎麼好好繼續往前走，當然這件事沒有任何人得到懲罰，只有受害的我帶著這件事爛在心裡腦裡。

即使這世界不會標籤你，你仍然會標籤自己，是不是我不夠好才會發生這種事？是不是有了這樣子的事情，我再不值得任何幸福的降臨？這樣的自己是不是很髒、很嘔心？我覺得這是每一個經歷性侵害後的人，都會丟給自己無限輪迴而且相似的問題，尤其是我們不敢說、沒有人可以說，其實我們的世界很黑很可怕，我們需要的是家人朋友的陪伴，教我們如果釋懷，而不是一直壓抑... 我說出這件事，是希望所有正在經歷、曾經經驗過類似事情的人，能夠勇敢的說出來，讓身邊的人知道你受傷、你痛，同時去阻止和杜絕這些 #施害者 繼續進行這些禽獸不如的行為。
我們都值得更好的，值得擁有幸福，我們仍然和一般人無異，至少我們愛惜自己，我們沒有濫交、沒有不自愛的亂搞、跑趴，我們仍然珍惜自己的生命，努力學習和成長，我們和大家沒有什麼不同。 -
我在2017年1月24日一個人走進手術室，拿掉不足一月的孩子，這件事從事發到結束僅有12天。
人生在世誰沒愛錯過幾個人？自己不長眼睛選的男朋友，和沒有保護好自己，確實是事實，也沒什麼好抱怨的，然而我想說的是關於「流產」這件事。
首先，我不覺得選擇人工流產是殘忍的，比起勉強把孩子生下來，爹不疼娘不愛、長輩也不喜歡，還沒有能力養活他，最後可能造成的人倫悲劇來說，我認為我的選擇是種仁慈，但我仍然無限悲痛。
再來，我認為不管是人為，抑或是自然流產，都需要被大量的關愛和陪伴，我發現的當時非常突然，剛好要準備去新工作、剛好要準備交接、剛好要準備過年了...事發後男生再也沒有出現過，當然也別談什麼負責和付費，完全沒有，而且在我人流後不到一個月，這個男的還讓另外一個女的懷孕了，半年就結婚，同年10月還11月誕下一個小女孩😅
而我從藥流到人流，都彷彿只有我一個人，工作上也是以感冒為由請假，基本上是沒有人知道和陪伴，爸爸是知情的，但在手術當天也忘記陪我，那真的是一件很可怕又很讓人歇斯底里的事，特別是護士想要安慰我而說出「你還年輕，你們現在不想要，以後還有機會」...那真的是比死更難受。
在等待到手術、到結束，唯一感受到的是從頭到腳的每個細胞都在撕裂的痛，而過後我仍然若無其事的上班、寫稿，為了不讓家人擔心，只有輕輕的一個擁抱哭了一下，然後日子每天每天過得比正常人還正常，工作比任何人都更積極勤奮，然後很快就除了自己再沒有人記得是那一天發生的事，也再不會有人提起。
2年來始終沒有停止的工作，總是在夜深人靜和一個人走在路上時，感覺悲痛的情緒來襲，但我仍然是一個人在面對。今年是第3個1月，我想面對它，我想開口說我仍然很難過，我想說我其實並不快樂。
我也希望如果你們身邊有各種原因而經歷這種不幸的人，請你們正面積極地給予大大的關懷與關心，不要相信「我沒事」「我很好」，不要以為一兩個簡單的擁抱就能告別所有傷痛，真的都是bullshit.😢 然後我一直很希望有人能和我一樣記得，小天使是1月16日終結的生命，1月24日完全離開，我希望能記住小天使來過的人，不只有我一個而已。
以上，是我生命中的2件小事，2件困擾我許久的小事，我始終相信面對傷痛，才會真正的痊癒，所以我要在新一年送給自己這份禮物，也請大家不必同情或者可憐我，因為有這些事才有現在的我，我很享受現在的自己，我覺得現在的我成長了，也比以前快樂了💗
突然來一發如此震撼的，不知道工作會不會有影響，但我還是很大膽的做了這件事，給自己生命一個出口，也謝謝你們看完這一篇，讓我公器私用的散佈了一下感傷😅
新的一年，我們都會更好的。
新的一年，我希望每一個人都能勇敢的面對人生。";;en;#metoo

即使這世界不會標籤你，你仍然會標籤自己，是不是我不夠好才會發生這種事？是不是有了這樣子的事情，我再不值得任何幸福的降臨？這樣的自己是不是很髒、很嘔心？我覺得這是每一個經歷性侵害後的人，都會丟給自己無限輪迴而且相似的問題，尤其是我們不敢說、沒有人可以說，其實我們的世界很黑很可怕，我們需要的是家人朋友的陪伴，教我們如果釋懷，而不是一直壓抑... 我說出這件事，是希望所有正在經歷、曾經經驗過類似事情的人，能夠勇敢的說出來，讓身邊的人知道你受傷、你痛，同時去阻止和杜絕這些  繼續進行這些禽獸不如的行為。
我們都值得更好的，值得擁有幸福，我們仍然和一般人無異，至少我們愛惜自己，我們沒有濫交、沒有不自愛的亂搞、跑趴，我們仍然珍惜自己的生命，努力學習和成長，我們和大家沒有什麼不同。 -
我在2017年1月24日一個人走進手術室，拿掉不足一月的孩子，這件事從事發到結束僅有12天。
人生在世誰沒愛錯過幾個人？自己不長眼睛選的男朋友，和沒有保護好自己，確實是事實，也沒什麼好抱怨的，然而我想說的是關於「流產」這件事。
首先，我不覺得選擇人工流產是殘忍的，比起勉強把孩子生下來，爹不疼娘不愛、長輩也不喜歡，還沒有能力養活他，最後可能造成的人倫悲劇來說，我認為我的選擇是種仁慈，但我仍然無限悲痛。
再來，我認為不管是人為，抑或是自然流產，都需要被大量的關愛和陪伴，我發現的當時非常突然，剛好要準備去新工作、剛好要準備交接、剛好要準備過年了...事發後男生再也沒有出現過，當然也別談什麼負責和付費，完全沒有，而且在我人流後不到一個月，這個男的還讓另外一個女的懷孕了，半年就結婚，同年10月還11月誕下一個小女孩😅
而我從藥流到人流，都彷彿只有我一個人，工作上也是以感冒為由請假，基本上是沒有人知道和陪伴，爸爸是知情的，但在手術當天也忘記陪我，那真的是一件很可怕又很讓人歇斯底里的事，特別是護士想要安慰我而說出「你還年輕，你們現在不想要，以後還有機會」...那真的是比死更難受。
在等待到手術、到結束，唯一感受到的是從頭到腳的每個細胞都在撕裂的痛，而過後我仍然若無其事的上班、寫稿，為了不讓家人擔心，只有輕輕的一個擁抱哭了一下，然後日子每天每天過得比正常人還正常，工作比任何人都更積極勤奮，然後很快就除了自己再沒有人記得是那一天發生的事，也再不會有人提起。
2年來始終沒有停止的工作，總是在夜深人靜和一個人走在路上時，感覺悲痛的情緒來襲，但我仍然是一個人在面對。今年是第3個1月，我想面對它，我想開口說我仍然很難過，我想說我其實並不快樂。
我也希望如果你們身邊有各種原因而經歷這種不幸的人，請你們正面積極地給予大大的關懷與關心，不要相信「我沒事」「我很好」，不要以為一兩個簡單的擁抱就能告別所有傷痛，真的都是bullshit.😢 然後我一直很希望有人能和我一樣記得，小天使是1月16日終結的生命，1月24日完全離開，我希望能記住小天使來過的人，不只有我一個而已。
以上，是我生命中的2件小事，2件困擾我許久的小事，我始終相信面對傷痛，才會真正的痊癒，所以我要在新一年送給自己這份禮物，也請大家不必同情或者可憐我，因為有這些事才有現在的我，我很享受現在的自己，我覺得現在的我成長了，也比以前快樂了💗
突然來一發如此震撼的，不知道工作會不會有影響，但我還是很大膽的做了這件事，給自己生命一個出口，也謝謝你們看完這一篇，讓我公器私用的散佈了一下感傷😅
新的一年，我們都會更好的。

新的一年，我希望每一個人都能勇敢的面對人生。";對傷痛才會痊癒 這是一篇文長而且非沉重的內容，首先感謝昨天在直播看我哭了很久的朋友們，一月對我來說真的太困難了；另外想請「極端的宗教朋友」、「道德魔人」、「酸民」們請先動動手退我的讚 / 追蹤，然後把頁面關閉，謝謝您。 這是我在2019年給自己的禮物，我不需要討拍、也不需要任何人的批評指教，我只是希望給自己的傷痛一個出口，同時也希望曾經和我經歷過類似事情的人，可以勇敢一些，身邊的朋友家人可以更正面積極的多陪伴一些，很多事真的不是一句沒關係、一個擁抱，就能讓傷痛不在了。 - column80: 'NN')];對傷痛才會痊癒 這是一篇文長而且非沉重的內容，首先感謝昨天在直播看我哭了很久的朋友們，一月對我來說真的太困難了；另外想請「極端的宗教朋友」、「道德魔人」、「酸民」們請先動動手退我的讚 / 追蹤，然後把頁面關閉，謝謝您。 這是我在2019年給自己的禮物，我不需要討拍、也不需要任何人的批評指教，我只是希望給自己的傷痛一個出口，同時也希望曾經和我經歷過類似事情的人，可以勇敢一些，身邊的朋友家人可以更正面積極的多陪伴一些，很多事真的不是一句沒關係、一個擁抱，就能讓傷痛不在了。 - . 是的，我在14歲（2007）時曾遭到一位香港某大電視台（現在仍在）的蘇姓龍虎舞師 侵害。 他利用家人和孩子的信任，以學武術為由，要求14歲的我和我的一位女同學，在晚上去海邊做體能訓練，並要求我們不穿內衣，同時用手機播放18禁影片給我們看，最後以神鬼說的因由把我帶到海中的浮台附近，繼而性侵得逞。 我承認14歲的時候真的是智商欠缺，不然也不會相信這種言論，在發現正在發生什麼的時候，已經來不及了 ... 事件過後我們當然再也沒有去學習過所謂的「武術」了，也因為我們拒絕學習，所以家人才會知道。 當時我爸說了一句「xx圈的人大不了就是上下其手，難不成你還給人家睡了」，為此我起碼恨了他6-8年，而當時身邊的朋友和同學卻是抱著懷疑態度拒絕相信有這樣的事情發生，甚至認為一個女生會為了討拍而捏造這種事，我為這些人的想法與思想感到可恥，其實我們需要的不是身邊的人去評價這件事，而是陪伴和告訴我們怎麼好好繼續往前走，當然這件事沒有任何人得到懲罰，只有受害的我帶著這件事爛在心裡腦裡。 即使這世界不會標籤你，你仍然會標籤自己，是不是我不夠好才會發生這種事？是不是有了這樣子的事情，我再不值得任何幸福的降臨？這樣的自己是不是很髒、很嘔心？我覺得這是每一個經歷性侵害後的人，都會丟給自己無限輪迴而且相似的問題，尤其是我們不敢說、沒有人可以說，其實我們的世界很黑很可怕，我們需要的是家人朋友的陪伴，教我們如果釋懷，而不是一直壓抑 ... 我說出這件事，是希望所有正在經歷、曾經經驗過類似事情的人，能夠勇敢的說出來，讓身邊的人知道你受傷、你痛，同時去阻止和杜絕這些 繼續進行這些禽獸不如的行為。 我們都值得更好的，值得擁有幸福，我們仍然和一般人無異，至少我們愛惜自己，我們沒有濫交、沒有不自愛的亂搞、跑趴，我們仍然珍惜自己的生命，努力學習和成長，我們和大家沒有什麼不同。 - - 人工流產。 我在2017年1月24日一個人走進手術室，拿掉不足一月的孩子，這件事從事發到結束僅有12天。 人生在世誰沒愛錯過幾個人？自己不長眼睛選的男朋友，和沒有保護好自己，確實是事實，也沒什麼好抱怨的，然而我想說的是關於「流產」這件事。 首先，我不覺得選擇人工流產是殘忍的，比起勉強把孩子生下來，爹不疼娘不愛、長輩也不喜歡，還沒有能力養活他，最後可能造成的人倫悲劇來說，我認為我的選擇是種仁慈，但我仍然無限悲痛。 再來，我認為不管是人為，抑或是自然流產，都需要被大量的關愛和陪伴，我發現的當時非常突然，剛好要準備去新工作、剛好要準備交接、剛好要準備過年了 ... 事發後男生再也沒有出現過，當然也別談什麼負責和付費，完全沒有，而且在我人流後不到一個月，這個男的還讓另外一個女的懷孕了，半年就結婚，同年10月還11月誕下一個小女孩😅 而我從藥流到人流，都彷彿只有我一個人，工作上也是以感冒為由請假，基本上是沒有人知道和陪伴，爸爸是知情的，但在手術當天也忘記陪我，那真的是一件很可怕又很讓人歇斯底里的事，特別是護士想要安慰我而說出「你還年輕，你們現在不想要，以後還有機會」 ... 那真的是比死更難受。 在等待到手術、到結束，唯一感受到的是從頭到腳的每個細胞都在撕裂的痛，而過後我仍然若無其事的上班、寫稿，為了不讓家人擔心，只有輕輕的一個擁抱哭了一下，然後日子每天每天過得比正常人還正常，工作比任何人都更積極勤奮，然後很快就除了自己再沒有人記得是那一天發生的事，也再不會有人提起。 2年來始終沒有停止的工作，總是在夜深人靜和一個人走在路上時，感覺悲痛的情緒來襲，但我仍然是一個人在面對。今年是第3個1月，我想面對它，我想開口說我仍然很難過，我想說我其實並不快樂。 我也希望如果你們身邊有各種原因而經歷這種不幸的人，請你們正面積極地給予大大的關懷與關心，不要相信「我沒事」「我很好」，不要以為一兩個簡單的擁抱就能告別所有傷痛，真的都是bullshit.😢 然後我一直很希望有人能和我一樣記得，小天使是1月16日終結的生命，1月24日完全離開，我希望能記住小天使來過的人，不只有我一個而已。 - 以上，是我生命中的2件小事，2件困擾我許久的小事，我始終相信面對傷痛，才會真正的痊癒，所以我要在新一年送給自己這份禮物，也請大家不必同情或者可憐我，因為有這些事才有現在的我，我很享受現在的自己，我覺得現在的我成長了，也比以前快樂了💗 突然來一發如此震撼的，不知道工作會不會有影響，但我還是很大膽的做了這件事，給自己生命一個出口，也謝謝你們看完這一篇，讓我公器私用的散佈了一下感傷😅 新的一年，我們都會更好的。 新的一年，我希望每一個人都能勇敢的面對人生。;對傷痛才會痊癒 這是一篇文長而且非沉重的內容，首先感謝昨天在直播看我哭了很久的朋友們，一月對我來說真的太困難了；另外想請「極端的宗教朋友」、「道德魔人」、「酸民」們請先動動手退我的讚 / 追蹤，然後把頁面關閉，謝謝您。 這是我在2019年給自己的禮物，我不需要討拍、也不需要任何人的批評指教，我只是希望給自己的傷痛一個出口，同時也希望曾經和我經歷過類似事情的人，可以勇敢一些，身邊的朋友家人可以更正面積極的多陪伴一些，很多事真的不是一句沒關係、一個擁抱，就能讓傷痛不在了。 - column1: i took a step in the right direction today. i healed a little bit.
i have a really long history of self harm. and today
column2: i got a tattoo to try and cover some of my scars.

column1: i won't go super into detail. i had a decently mentally rough childhood and it broke me every day. but forgiveness is everything
column2: and i've decided to start forgiving myself.
someone i had trusted violated me personally. he raped me. and tried to deny it. i lived in fear and terror while he blamed the act on me. i lived with him for a month afterwards
column3: terrified he would touch me again. and he did

column1: it is awful to wake up and have your inner thighs soaked in semen
column2: with no idea how it got there.

column1: he was a cna - soon to be nurse. everyone trusted him. i never pressed charges. i'm just a girl with too many cats - who would listen?
so i moved. i left a job i loved
column3: and started somewhere new - hopefully away from the memories and the heartache.

column1: i have nightmares every couple nights. i cry and wonder why. but i've started to forgive myself
column2: even if i can't forgive or forget him and what he did.

column1: 84092;instagram;2019-01-09 05:24:04;FALSE;"the marine corps. has a lot of work to do regarding its leadership. i'm proud to see that our female marine community has gained the strength to openly challenge these sexist remarks publically so that the usmc is held accountable to the public. the top of any organization sets the tone for its subordinates.  it's time that this behavior is addressed. our women deserve leaders they can trust and admire especially when so many of us have been abused. military sexual trauma is cultural. mst literally causes suicides
column2: substance abuse and homelessness in the female veteran community. we spend much of our time helping each other through our struggles. ones that we shouldn't even be facing on our own. we are often the ones neglected. our stories are the ones that remain untold and our lives often the ones forgotten. our fighting back is a strong message to the establishment that we are no longer tolerating poor leadership that openly disrespects women.

column2: so if you've known me for a while
column3: you would know that i use to be a huge r. kelly fan.  so much so
column4: that the license plate on my car read ""rkllyfn"" (r. kelly fan). since the lifetime docuseries aired last week
column5: my phone has been blowing up.  i've had people contact me that i haven't heard from in years calling/texting me asking me my thoughts.  well
column6: here it is.  psa...i am no longer an r. kelly fan!!! #periodttt  watching those six episodes made me sick to my stomach.  this man allowed his abuse as a young child turn him into a monster and everyone around him fed the monster enabling him to do what he did to countless young girls and women.  the crazy thing is
column7: i've actually been to that studio in like 2000 when i use to be in the music industry.  it is very clear now that the real reason why the ""timing wasn't right"" was because i or my client weren't seen as easy pray for his sick ass shenanigans.  god has always had my back...even when i didn't understand it.  i actually stopped being an r. kelly fan back in 2011 once i read the book ""the man behind the man"" written by his personal assistant that was in the docuseries.  that book was very compelling and i believed he was a monster then
column8: just not on the level he's on now.  i was still able to listen to his music because i told myself that i could separate the man from the music.  well
column9: this is no longer the case.  i have deleted any playlists that i had with his music on it.  it actually makes me sick to my stomach when i hear his music now.  i have a daughter and if i continued to support this man
column10: it would be sending her a horrible message as to what is acceptable when it comes to the treatment from a man.  i apologize to my daughter this day for not doing this sooner.  like when i saw the marriage certificate surface between he and aaliyah.  i'm drained and i'm done after watching #survivingrkelly #survivor #muterkelly #effrkelly #fuckrkelly #blackgirlsmatter #metoo";;en;#periodttt

column1: 84105;instagram;2019-01-09 05:38:45;FALSE;here’s to being real and finally having the courage to share my story
column3: to have others think that you’re damaged. you see
column4: the girl on the left is someone who i left in the past
column5: someone who i neglected to remember
column6: because it brought back a million memories of the time that i could not breathe. it wasn’t until about a year ago that i volunteered at a domestic violence center
column7: that i realized that i wasn’t completely healed. i was in a toxic relationship that was very abusive
column10: and mental. i struggled to see the damage
column11: because i felt like i had to be strong
column13: trying to smile as if nothing was wrong. no one around me knew what was going on. i didn’t want anyone to know. i didn’t want to be the girl that i learned about in health class
column14: i told myself i would never be her
column15: but the thing is that i was her. i didn’t have the courage to leave
column16: until i had no choice. i switched cars with my mom
column18: and i had made a new friend who protected me at work👮🏻‍♀️♥️. it’s crazy how people are placed in your life. it took some time
column19: i grasped the little strength that i had left inside me. & i began climbing mountains
column22: finally having the courage to join a gym
column23: using my struggles to fuel me. i’ve always had this little fire in me
column24: it’s crazy the strength you gain when you just want to breathe. i wanted to fly
column28: to be an example for my sister
column29: & to leave the past behind me. i don’t regret my past decisions
column30: i wouldn’t be who i am today. scars and all but i’m happy
column31: i am strong. the gym has helped me in so many ways
column32: and i can’t thank fitness and nutrition enough. it’s a lifestyle that leads to much more than aesthetics
column33: it leads to self love. & all around strength. it helps rebuild you from the ground up. i know many of us hide our struggles
column34: we are all faced with different challenges
column35: but its not about what happens to us
column36: but about how we choose to react. one step at a time

column1: 2019年1月3日 【am730專欄】kevin spacey在剛過去的平安夜在youtube上載了一段被外媒形容為「bizarre video」的三分鐘自述影片《let me be frank》，我好奇點進去看，哎……是真的……bizarre…… 有追看《紙牌屋》的朋友，一定知道kevin spacey在戲裡的角色名字就是「frank」，《let me be frank》這片名玩一語雙關，既是說自己在這視頻中演釋的是frank（須知道因為性侵醜聞kevin spacey已被踢出《紙牌屋》劇組），也語帶雙關地暗示他要對所有衝他而來的醜聞be frank — 坦白地訴說一下。
於是在這條《let me be frank》的視頻裡，大家看見的kevin spacey應該不是kevin spacey，而是frank，事實上視頻裡的kevin spacey在開放式廚房背景下穿著圍裙，演著一邊做菜一邊說話的獨腳戲，但frank說的話，卻明顯是在替kevin spacey叫囂。
叫囂什麼呢？「if i didn't pay the price for things we both know i did do
column2: i'm certainly not going to pay the price for the things i didn't do.」 所以他是在否認對他的性侵指控吧？

column1: 為什麼說這條視頻怪異，因為kevin spacey這名字、這個人是帶著極高商業價值的，不是普羅大眾一般網民，遇事心有不甘，隨便懶叻地拍一條視頻呼冤，《let me be frank》這條視頻肯定是公關手腕，但怪異在於這公關手段的目的是什麼？
視頻裡的kevin spacey/ frank看來絕不友善，甚至可以說是有點恐怖，語調威嚇神色挑釁，完全達不到因為被冤枉而盼望公平審訊的公關目的，以戲中戲來陳述，更是缺乏誠意兼過火的形式，一語雙關的標題看似醒目，實質有點幼稚。
想來想去，這條視頻大概是想告訴大家 — kevin spacey確實很好戲？

視頻裡的kevin spacey/ frank看來絕不友善，甚至可以說是有點恐怖，語調威嚇神色挑釁，完全達不到因為被冤枉而盼望公平審訊的公關目的，以戲中戲來陳述，更是缺乏誠意兼過火的形式，一語雙關的標題看似醒目，實質有點幼稚。

column1: 84133;instagram;2019-01-09 04:36:09;FALSE;my days have all been blending together since i started treatment - i’m exhausted all the time😩 but i’m so grateful for this opportunity and how everything fell into place for me. i met with the psychiatrist today and i found out they want to change my medication. i’m currently taking 60mg of prozac and they want to put me back to 40mg to help me not feel so numb. this makes me nervous bc the last time i was at 40mg
column2: the medicine really messed with me. i was so depressed and suicidal. i couldn’t get out of bed or bring myself to shower regularly. it was a very dark time for me.. has anyone else experienced something similar to this? how did you handle it? was the outcome successful for you? #treatment #thisiswhatrecoverylookslike #bulimia #depression #eatingdisorder #anorexia #bingeeatingdisorderrecovery #bodyacceptance #depressionquotes #relatable #youareenough #poetry #anxiety #pain #struggle #lifewithouted #recovery #medication #prozac #lamictal #psychiatrist #ocd #bulimiarecovery #selflove #selfacceptance #compassion #nonjudgemental #emotion #metoo #stronger;;en;#treatment

84147;instagram;2019-01-09 04:50:26;FALSE;january is stalking awareness month. because i have been personally affected by stalking for the last 5.5 years i feel it’s important to share some facts and tips about stalking this month.

the use of technology to stalk and the workplace by maya raghu: stalking is generally a course of conduct directed at a specific person that would cause a reasonable person to feel fear. stalking behavior includes
column2: but is not limited to: following or spying on a person
column3: waiting at places in order to make unwanted contact with the victim or to monitor the victim
column4: leaving unwanted items and gifts for the victim
column5: and posting information or spreading rumors about the victim on the internet
column7: or by word of mouth. stalking is strongly correlated to sexual assault and domestic violence. approximately 1 in 6 women (16.2%) and 1 in 19 men (5.2%) in the united states have been victims of stalking. nearly three out of four stalking victims knew his or her offender in some capacity and 21.5% of stalking victims identified their stalker as a former intimate. #stalkingawarenessmonth #nsam #stalkingawareness #cyberstalking #awareness #breakthesilence #stopblamingvictims #metoo #sexualassault #january #imafighter #nobackingdown #stalking #stalkers #advocate";;en;#stalkingawarenessmonth

column1: 84159;instagram;2019-01-08 18:33:04;FALSE;"#breaking story from the field! young female at risk of trafficking intercepted at bus park in nepal! ⠀
18-year-old pareli was living in poverty with relatives when she was sexually abused by one of them. because she no longer felt safe at home
column2: she tried to live with another relative but had similar circumstances that made her feel lonely and abandoned by everyone.⠀
she met a boy online through facebook. they started sharing their thoughts and feelings with each other
column3: and they soon became good friends. the boy told her that he was working in a hotel in india and offered her a job there. without informing anyone
column4: she ran away from her sister's house to meet him.⠀

column1: while she was waiting for him at the station
column2: our staff saw her and started questioning her. at first
column3: she lied to them saying that she had come from another district and was waiting for her relative who was coming to pick her up. our staff brought her to the booth and called her family to verify her story. after the truth was revealed
column4: she was taken to a shelter and was provided counseling. she is now in a safe environment and is knowledgeable about the dangers of human trafficking! ⠀

column1: child sexual abuse 👇 👇🏽 👇🏾 👇🏿 child sexual abuse is an issue that makes people extremely uncomfortable
column2: because it hurts to think about anyone harming children. however
column3: unreported or untreated child sexual abuse not only scars children and destroys families
column4: it also leaves offenders free to abuse and cripple future generations.

column1: it is any sexual activity between adults and minors or between two minors when one forces it on the other. this includes sexual touching and non-touching acts like exhibitionism
column3: photography of a child for sexual gratification
column4: solicitation of a child for prostitution
column5: voyeurism and communication in a sexual way by phone
column6: internet or face-to-face. it is a crime punishable by law that must be reported.

column1: how often does child sexual abuse take place? fact: the real prevalence of child sexual abuse is not known because so many victims do not disclose or report their abuse. researchers have suggested rates varying from 1% to 35%. most professionals in the field of abuse use rates from 8% to 20%.fact: even if the true prevalence of child sexual abuse is not known
column2: most will agree that there will be 500
column3: 000 babies born in the us this year that will be sexually abused before they turn 18 if we do not prevent it.adult retrospective studies show that 1 in 4 women and 1 in 6 men were sexually abused before the age of 18 (centers for disease control and prevention
column4: 2006). this means there are more than 42 million adult survivors of child sexual abuse in the u.s.the primary reason that the public is not sufficiently aware of child sexual abuse as a problem is that 73% of child victims do not tell anyone about the abuse for at least a year. 45% of victims do not tell anyone for at least 5 years. some never disclose !

column1: 84246;instagram;2019-01-09 02:18:44;FALSE;"after having a clear vision for 2018 here is what i did with my year 🔸 had a tamil movie release - kkpk. i made it to the big screen and also made it on the movie poster 🔸 stopped working for anyone else.

🔸 leased my own 2 bedroom apartment and furnished it to my own liking with a separate home office - no more flatmate’s weee. 🔸incorporated my own social media advertising company - sabby jey social on 23rd may 2018. in 6 months i grew to manage 10 companies
column2: majority of them turning over millions in revenue. on 11th december i signed with global digital advertising company reach local as an affiliate company to provide social content creation for some clients. by the end of the year i tripled my hourly rate (touch wood it stays that way might have its ups and downs). 🔸 started acting classes in new zealand and thoroughly learned a few fundamental techniques. 🔸 2 grips to sydney. 🔸 became an ambassador for caci clinic and huawei mobile nz. 🔸 gave to motivational talks one for caci beauty and one about being authentic for the pan asian screen collective. 🔸spent less time on “being successful” and built more time on building meaningful relationships 🔸hit 24.5k on instagram close to a quarter of 100k my goal. 🔸 decorated my room and apartment  the way i want and worked towards one of my goals “live beautifully.” hard blows 🔸 funded myself through six weeks of being in and out of hospital from being incredibly ill. 🔸 healed from my first very serious relationship that didn’t work out and spent my year single. 🔸 the hardest - joined #metoo by having the courage to file a case against someone who sexually assaulted me. 🔸 spent 3 months searching for a suitable apartment and lugged my shit around between temporary accomodation
column3: friends spare bedrooms and my parents lounge floor in sydney.

column1: i laid out a lot more goals for myself and did get tempted to be hard on myself for not getting there but honestly i moved forward and i got further than i did in 2017. just working towards what you love matters success will follow.
goals for 2019 > coming soon still gotta think.

column1: i bought a fitbit not because i wanted to know how many steps i  take (it’s a lot when you’re pacing around like an armadillo trying to wipe a toddlers butt and put a baby to sleep at the same time). i bought it to challenge the story i had around sleep and the limiting beliefs that were impacting my reality.
@tonyrobbins taught me the first thing to do when trying to change a behaviour is to look at the beliefs .. and to change a belief look for all the evidence to the contrary.
having ptsd from a non sleeping first child
column2: i knew i needed to see the actual evidence of how much sleep i’m getting versus the beliefs and stories in my head. and it’s been game changing. no more endless thought patterns of ‘i’m tired and i can’t do this’. rather ‘i got x hours of sleep last night and even though i feel a bit shit now
column3: i should have enough in the bank to get through’. as womxn we have to contend not only with the beliefs we create ourselves but all the beliefs created for us. beliefs like ‘i’m not pretty or worthy of loveable’ beliefs like ‘she can but i can’t’.. these are part of an organised system of oppression (called patriarchy) that i for one am sick to death of. while we are too busy feeling guilty or ashamed or fat or tired
column4: the people in charge of these systems are literally strangling the earth and fighting wars and selling us stuff we don’t need.

column1: 84329;instagram;2019-01-09 01:18:07;FALSE;"*disclaimer: this post have nothing to do with this picture but sometimes you have to accompany a horrible experience with a good memory* it is long but please read!
to the guy who called me a “fat a**”
column2: “a sl*t” and told me that “no one would ever love me with my big mouth” and to “mind my own business” at the gas station as i asked you to leave the young lady you were harassing alone: your opinion doesn’t define me.

column1: i don’t remember what i said to you but it doesn’t matter because i love every bit of myself and your empty words don’t mean sh*t to me!
to the girl who hugged me while crying after you were safe while saying “i am so scared
column2: i thought he was going to hurt us”: i was also terrified but together we are stronger.

column1: to the people that just stood around or even worse got in your cars and left: you need to do better!
violence against anyone regardless of sex
column5: religion or beliefs should offend and affect every single one of us. we can’t normalize violence because it has become common
column6: we can’t dehumanize ourselves because today it was a young lady who i didn’t know but tomorrow it could be you!

column1: if you see someone in danger please call 911 🙏

column2: i thought he was going to hurt us”: i was also terrified but together we are stronger.

column6: we can’t dehumanize ourselves because today it was a young lady who i didn’t know but tomorrow it could be you!

column3: i will be launching a help group to help people who have been victimized by the personal training (fitness) industry.  i recently on-boarded some new clients. one client mentioned that she started working out with a male trainer and he began to call and text her in a non-professional manner. all this occurred after one session. she may have worked out with him twice
column4: but anyhow she found me. this trainer is not located in delaware. this help group is for women and men alike. we (undisclosed partnership) want to hear your stories. we want you to recover. we want you to get your lives back. it is not okay. 🔹🔹🔹more details are coming🔹🔹🔹you can inbox or message me with any questions. we support you. 💪🏾if anything
column5: i  can refer you to a great mh therapist located in new castle to assist with your healing. you can do this.

column1: reviewed by andrew chan (film critics circle of australia)
the biggest problem with shane black’s latest reboot of “predator” is coherency and with so much controversy surrounding the film in the midst of the #metoo movement
column2: the film ended up as one big mess. with so much backstory and character development ended up on the cutting floor
column3: the film despite containing a fairly ambitious script ends up being cliche and even at times laughable. random events and characters suddenly appears and slowly destroying any emotional attachment the audience may have for the characters.

column1: boyd holbrook headlines the feature and ends up left behind in terms of charisma and presence for the rest of the cast. olivia munn portray the strong heroine role
column2: but loses out in the lack of any character development. for the ensemble cast of military guys (trevante rhodes
column5: thomas jane) we get entertaining performance and play off between the group
column6: but ultimately feels like it is from another better film.

column2: “predator” tries too hard to link up previous films and events in an attempt to create a money spinning franchise. unfortunately it is a box office bomb and is unlikely to see its planned sequels made. we try to picture what kind of film
column4: but it ended up far to scratchy

column1: looking forward to engaging miranda pilipchuk’s work on gender violence as she challenges
column2: what i refer to in my commentary as the “second wave” of the #metoo movement. my intervention will focus on the “domestic problem of alterity” and use the bill cosby case to challenge pilipchuk’s notion that #metoo is different from international discourses surrounding violence against women in that it primarily focuses on white women as survivors of gender violence
column3: individual white men “behaving badly” and participated in this notion of american exceptionalism as it concerns the global problem of violence against women (pilipchuk’s argument).";;en;#MeToo

column2: south carolina thought that powerhouse alabama would win their 5th national championship in 8-years. the general consensus was most people wanted clemson
column3: but didn’t think they could win the game against the colossal titan.

column1: wow were they wrong. clemson completely dominated the defending national champion and annihilated the crimson tide 44-16.
i believe there are 3 reasons why clemson won the game and became the only team in college football history to go 15-0 in a season: 🏈
1. clemson culture. it’s clear that the players love playing for coach dabo swinney and his staff. as a matter of fact
column2: when you look at the clemson culture
column3: there is tremendous consistency. in 5 years
column4: there have only been a total of 3 coaching changes on the entire clemson staff. impressive.

column2: there have been 20 coaching changes on staff in the same 5 year period. wow. that’s a big difference. culture and consistency. #allin

column1: 2. “serve their hearts…not their talents.” commentator chris fowler said this is how dabo swinney coaches his players. it’s clear that both teams have extraordinary athletes with tons of talent. it’s also clear that coach swinney appeals to the hearts of his players and you can see the emotion and temperament they play with and the love and respect they have for their coach.
3. leaders make tough decisions. in week 4 of this season
column2: dabo swinney named qb trevor lawrence the starter over incumbent kelly bryant. coach swinney saw something in the young true freshman qb that made him believe lawrence could direct and lead this team to where it had not been the previous year.

column1: great coaches not only can assess talent
column2: but they trust their gut and sometimes make unpopular decisions. this decision turned out to be better than nostradamus could have predicted!” thanks td!!!

column2: mostrando porque eu sempre digo que não posso pentear o cabelo
column3: demos boas risadas com isso e pronto
column4: acabou o papo. mas depois eu fiquei olhando mais um pouco essa foto e pensando quanta força e significado tinha ali
column5: era muito mais que uma piada. pra quem me conhece a mais tempo
column6: deve lembrar do cabelo liso e comprido
column7: mantido a base de muita química e horas de secador e chapinha
column8: foram anos de maus tratos para me enquadrar dentro do padrão convencionado pela sociedade. até que eu cansei
column11: aceitei e compreendi que eu não precisava me curvar aos padrões
column12: e ninguém precisa. não é só a transição capilar
column13: não é só um cabelo liso
column15: é uma transição que vem de dentro pra fora
column16: é uma compreensão e apropriação das nossas vidas e corpos
column17: e o que representamos diante da sociedade. é ser o que sentimos uma genuína vontade de ser
column18: é compreender que cada uma tem seu tempo e a sua forma de externar isso
column19: é ter a certeza que você pode passar uma vida a base de progressiva
column20: e se isso te faz se sentir bem
column21: também tá ótimo. quem define suas verdades é você
column22: no seu tempo. mas eu não compreendi tudo isso sozinha
column23: e essa é a parte mais linda dessa transformação
column24: é olhar para trás e perceber quantas mulheres maravilhosas me ajudaram a descobrir isso
column25: me incentivaram ou apenas me impactaram nas redes com as suas descobertas e desconstrução diária. entendi o verdadeiro significado de sororidade
column26: e sei o impacto que isso teve na mulher que sou hoje
column28: na minha autoconfiança e nas minhas lutas. e por isso eu escrevo hoje
column29: primeiro pra todas as manas saberem o quanto foram
column30: e continuam sendo fundamentais. e mais importante que isso

column1: 84478;instagram;2019-01-08 22:42:13;FALSE;"journaling is one of those things i’ve always had good intentions about most of my life but never stuck with...until now. 💗⁣

i’ve been fully inspired on this journey i’m on and have been non-stop journaling for over a month. it is so therapeutic and i think so many people would benefit from putting pen to paper daily...getting your thoughts onto paper
it’s been such a game changer for me that i wanted to create something for anyone that wants to journal but not sure where to start. ⁣
i’ve created a free simple “30 days of journaling prompts” guide for anyone that wants it! ⁣
if you’ve been thinking about starting journaling or want to experience its greatness in your life just sign up at the link in my bio and the guide will come directly to your email for free! ✨🙌🏻💞⁣

column1: stephan watched in front of the school as the young mother kissed her four children goodbye. my mother was oblivious to his plotting and scheming to become a part of her existence. every day he found ways to make contact with her. a seemingly accidental meeting got them on speaking terms and consistently crossing paths made it feel natural to stop and have a chat for a moment.
feeling confident that he had established a rapport with the young mother
column2: he blatantly followed her home one day. sophia
column4: stopped and playfully teased him about following her. he continued to walk her home as they joked about him being a stalker.

column2: and i was seven years old
column3: the day my mother invited stephan into our home. it was the beginning of my nightmare. through my eyes i want to bring to your attention a man that watched
column4: stalked and preyed on my family and many other families. it was his intentions all along to violate the sanctity of our family for his own self gratification.

column1: after you have read my story
column2: you will grab your children and cover them with a blanket of protection because just when you thought he was a part of a childish fairytale
column3: you find out the boogey man does exist………

column1: child sexual abuse 👇 👇🏽 👇🏾 👇🏿 child sexual abuse is an issue that makes people extremely uncomfortable
column2: because it hurts to think about anyone harming children. however
column3: unreported or untreated child sexual abuse not only scars children and destroys families
column4: it also leaves offenders free to abuse and cripple future generations.

column1: it is any sexual activity between adults and minors or between two minors when one forces it on the other. this includes sexual touching and non-touching acts like exhibitionism
column3: photography of a child for sexual gratification
column4: solicitation of a child for prostitution
column5: voyeurism and communication in a sexual way by phone
column6: internet or face-to-face. it is a crime punishable by law that must be reported.

column1: how often does child sexual abuse take place? fact: the real prevalence of child sexual abuse is not known because so many victims do not disclose or report their abuse. researchers have suggested rates varying from 1% to 35%. most professionals in the field of abuse use rates from 8% to 20%.fact: even if the true prevalence of child sexual abuse is not known
column2: most will agree that there will be 500
column3: 000 babies born in the us this year that will be sexually abused before they turn 18 if we do not prevent it.adult retrospective studies show that 1 in 4 women and 1 in 6 men were sexually abused before the age of 18 (centers for disease control and prevention
column4: 2006). this means there are more than 42 million adult survivors of child sexual abuse in the u.s.the primary reason that the public is not sufficiently aware of child sexual abuse as a problem is that 73% of child victims do not tell anyone about the abuse for at least a year. 45% of victims do not tell anyone for at least 5 years. some never disclose !

column1: a federal lawsuit filed in new york accuses republican presidential candidate donald trump of repeatedly raping a 13-year-old girl more than 20 years ago
column2: at several upper east side parties hosted by convicted sex offender and notorious billionaire investor jeffrey epstein.
first reported by the real deal
column3: accuses trump and epstein of luring the anonymous plaintiff and other young women to four parties at epstein’s so-called wexner mansion at 9 east 71st street. epstein allegedly lured the plaintiff
column4: identified in the suit only as jane doe
column5: with promises of a modeling career and cash.

column2: identified in additional testimony as tiffany doe
column4: testifying that she met epstein at port authority
column5: where he hired her to recruit other young girls for his parties. trump had known epstein for seven years in 1994 when he attended the parties at wexner
column6: according to the suit. he also allegedly knew that the plaintiff was 13 years old.

column1: jane doe filed a similar suit in california in april
column3: also accusing trump and epstein of rape. that suit was dismissed on the grounds of improper paperwork — the address affiliated with her name was found to be abandoned. today’s suit confirms that the plaintiffs are one and the same.

column1: ·  how to make sure you find out right away if a serious problem exists without spending all of your time listening to complaints;

column1: 84602;instagram;2019-01-08 21:03:41;FALSE;"when you run an amazing company that is making the world a better place
column2: one of the last things you probably want to hear is that an employee feels harassed or discriminated against. but
column3: statistics show that harassment and discrimination occur at very high rates
column4: and good companies are not immune. after the #metoo movement many business owners with scaling companies worry they might lose good employees or even face lawsuits because of discrimination
column5: but they’re not ready to hire a full human resources department. in this presentation
column6: meredith holley describes the three steps that work to stop and prevent toxic work environments including: ·  how to actively diagnose whether a work environment is toxic or healthy;

column1: ·  how to make sure you find out right away if a serious problem exists without spending all of your time listening to complaints;
·  how to effectively respond to employee issues without losing good employees;
·  why investigations alone are not enough to respond to complaints at work; and
·  why understanding and navigating the power dynamics of the work environment are key skills for every employee to learn in order to stop and prevent toxic work environments.

column2: this presentation gets you started creating cultural health in your company.

column1: 84617;instagram;2019-01-08 21:10:13;FALSE;"it can be difficult to be a feminist and lover of music. 🎧

column2: i have loved rock and emo music but it hasn't always been a welcoming experience. from feeling uncomfortable at mostly male gigs
column3: to lyrics that put women down
column4: to male friends who would assume that i was only pretending to like bands to impress boys
column5: to realising so many of my favourite bands were men
column6: to finding out as an adult that the men that made the songs i liked had abusive reputations: misogyny has always loomed large.

column1: and this isn't just a rock issue.

column2: this is the case in every popular genre of music. this is because popular music
column3: like a lot of art forms
column4: has long shut woman creators out
column5: excluding them from the industry and devaluing their music.

column1: but today in the world of online music we
column4: more access to music without gatekeepers
column5: more ways to share and find unrepresented talents.

column1: we can make sure we are aware of who the people behind the music are
column2: we can demand they are held to account for their actions and we can refuse to listen to the music of abusers.

column1: we can vote with our ears and listen to diverse artists that reflect our experiences
and this is what i plan to do! who would you recommend? 🎶

column1: this is me. authentically unapologetically me. i have nothing to hide. for so long i hid from myself. i laid in solitude with my secrets. it was a lonely place to be. but i don’t want to hide anymore. i want everyone to see me. all of me.

when i was 9 years old a man i barely knew got into my bed. i was asleep and i was woken up by his touch. this was not the first time he put his hands on me but this was the first time he came into my bed and did it. this time i knew it was wrong. i was 9
column2: he was in his 40’s. i was a child and in that moment my innocence was taken. stolen. i remember trying to scream but no sound came from my mouth. i knew my voice would save me and so i tried again and again until i found it. i’m one of the lucky ones. i spoke up that night and that was the end of it. this all happened under the care of my aunt. when i told her what happened she informed the police immediately but then told me that i could never tell anyone what happened to me. she made me promise. so i did what she told me. i lived in silence.  what she didn’t realise is with one promise she took my voice away. the same voice that saved me that night. she silenced it. it’s taken me 20 years to find that voice again and now that i’ve found it you best believe i’m going to use it.

column1: 84660;instagram;2019-01-08 20:46:57;FALSE;"during the last weeks a few people in my life opened up to me about their experiences with sexual assault and
column3: i am trying to help but at the same time
column4: have to acknowledge that i'm limited in my ability to do so. sexual violence is deeply rooted in our western culture - if we want it or not. it's in the media
column6: in our schools and workplaces. it's making sure victims aren't making anyone ""uncomfortable"" and teaching young girls to ""not do anything wrong that could make somebody assault you"". it's watching some people thrive in their life and others crumble. everything about it is uncomfortable & frustrating. still... i am privileged talking about it. cause i am white
column9: i am educated and have enough money to pay my rent and still afford myself some luxury. yeah i have issues but i also got several doctors and cheap health insurance. i am so damn lucky and also have this little platform to talk about issues that are important to me. sometimes i still feel overwhelmed and helpless. when i opened up about my own abuse i started getting messages. first i felt pretty powerless but now i really wanna create things that encourage people to seek help or start a conversation. i think that pop culture can encourage people confront their feelings and find words for their pain. so if you know someone that struggles or if you're the one please know that you're not alone. it happened to most of us but we were raised to not talk about it and pretend that nothing happened. your pain is valid and so are all the happy moments you had since then cause you are so much more than your abusers victim. never feel bad for the good days
column10: they don't make your story less true. i don't know if it helps or makes your day a little better but i wrote this song about my own assault as part on my bachelors degree. (it’s on #spotify) it felt really freeing back then and today
column11: after a conversation with a friend
column12: i even managed to listen to it for the first time without feeling sick to my bones. i guess that's personal growth and i hope that you find someone to talk to. if not my inbox is always open. 🌙

column1: 84675;instagram;2019-01-08 20:04:24;FALSE;"you ever feel like society makes it hard to exist? 🙄
bc i feel that way. that im too much of something or not enough of something else. there is always someone's label i don't fit or box i don't fit in. it gets tiring and over the years
column2: i've felt just how much it drains on my energy.  it makes me sad that i've gone through my whole life shaping who i am based on a false definition of beauty. a false definition of what it means to be a woman. american has put too many unrealistic expectations and destructive standards on both our men and women and we have to break them. we have to learn
column4: and rebuild ourselves. intimidating someone to stop harassing/abusing/assaulting/killing others
column5: and teaching them how to be comfortable in themselves enough to not need to worry about others is 2 different fights. both are needed. and i support both 🖤 but my job and passion is about teaching others to love themselves so much
column6: they never forget to love themselves. and in turn the world becomes a better place.

column1: 84702;instagram;2019-01-04 06:48:39;FALSE;"it wasn't my fault that i was assaulted three times
column2: but that doesn't mean i have to sit down and wait for a fourth. it doesn't mean i can't take control of my healing process or find justice and closure when the justice system isn't a good option for me. it's taken me a long time to find closure for the last two assaults
column3: and i'm currently in the process of finding closure for the first assault. for me
column4: i wanted all three attackers to know that what they did was wrong
column5: but i was only able to confront two of them. i forgave them when they apologized for hurting me
column6: and i didn't pursue anything legal because life had already dealt them their consequences. it was enough for me
column7: to make sure they were taking steps to have this never happen again. but the first one moved out of my reach before i realized what had happened to me. he went to the navy
column8: and i can't get to him except informally. the navy has been wonderful in listening to my story
column10: and making sure this follows him. if he hurts anyone else
column11: my story will be there to point at a history. that's the best that i can do
column12: and i have found joy in making sure he is held accountable for his actions and attitudes towards women. forgiveness is important to move on
column13: but that doesn't mean i give up fighting to make sure this never happens again

column1: 84703;instagram;2019-01-05 23:25:02;FALSE;2018 was a rough year for me. two semesters ago
column2: i was sexually assaulted. i have been very open talking about this. it’s something that needs to be talked about. april 18. i’ll never forget that date now. it took me 2 days to come forward and tell my family. it happened with someone who i was friends with for some years. i knew the statistics of 1/5 college women are sexually assaulted and most of the time it’s from someone you already know. i knew the feelings of guilt
column4: and everything else that other victims have talked about
column5: but i still felt all of them. after going through a school hearing
column7: and an appeal right after it happened
column8: i am still living on a campus with the male who assaulted me. every time i leave my house
column9: i have to worry if i am going to see him. i must watch what i say as to not be “charged with harassment from the respondent” and be aware of what “i say about the campus”. i have to take a back stairwell as to ensure i don’t see him. i have to participate in a club remotely because i cannot go to the meetings with him there and the school cannot tell him he can’t do something because “he is still an enrolled student on campus.” if he is at an event before i get there
column10: i must be the one to leave. mutual no contacts are not enough! all it does is victimize. this has made me stronger than i could have ever imagined. i forget that a lot
column11: but i’m working on it. god gives his hardest situations to those with the strongest hearts. to everyone reading this
column12: be more aware of your relationships and surroundings
column13: please. you won’t think it’ll happen to you until it does. to anyone who has been sexually assaulted or harmed in anyway
column14: you are not alone. you can reach out to me. to everyone who has supported me through this whole thing and continues to do so

column1: 84710;instagram;2019-01-08 18:32:39;FALSE;"have you watched ‘surviving r kelly’ yet? if you feel able to

the documentary highlights how as a society we fail black women time and time again. we don’t socially perceive black girls and women as innocent and we don’t trust or believe their testimony’s. this is not only true of the juror who explicitly said he didn’t believe the victims because of their appearance or how they spoke – in other words because they are black.

column2: all of us who have ignored these women’s stories
column3: including the numerous artists who have continued to work with r kelly
column4: need to take a hard look at why we have been willing to pass these women’s stories off as “rumors”. surviving r kelly also brings to the fore the inextricable link between sex and power. the brave testimony’s of the survivors highlights how sex can be (and often is) used as a means of dominating. we need to be looking more deeply and more critically at this link so that we can more fully understand sexual abuse

column1: we absolutely cannot separate r kellys music from his abuse. he has trailers at his video shoots and built bedrooms in his studio where he held and abused underage girls
column2: and then he wrote songs like ‘bump n grind’
column3: ‘it seems like your ready’ ‘age ain’t nothing but a number’ these songs are all about abusing girls. this is indeed hiding in plain sight.

column1: men like this feel they are untouchable in part because they are rich. r kelly is able to afford payoffs
column2: lawyers and nda’s because of the revenue he continually receives from support of his music. he has also been able to hide behind the status he has achieved as an artist (from songs about abusing children). let us stand as allies with these survivors. joining the @officialmuterkelly movement first and foremost
column3: but also really looking at why we do not trust and believe or care fully for black women and girls and woc more widely
column4: and looking at why we are so quick to excuse or ignore womens accounts in favour of shielding men (artists or otherwise) from being held accountable for the abuse.

یعنی با زدن حجاب، چنان بلایی به سر زن آوردن که زن امروز نیازمند یک منجیه!
این میشه که پولساز ترین سلبریتی‌های غرب مثل لیدی گاگا رو فرش قرمز با کت مردونه بیگ سایز میاد که بگه من آلت دست نیستم!

و قابل خرید و فروش هستند،زن به مثابه کالا تلقی میشه ! کالایی که مانند اپل و پاناسونیک و تسلا باید در بالاترین کیفیت به مرد عرضه بشه ! حالا کمپانی های عظیم : مد و آرایش و جراحی های افسارگسیخته،از نوک ناخن پا، و انواع و اقسام کاشت های ناخن تا زیورآلات مچ پا و آرایش ساق پا کشیدگی پوست و خالکوبی و برداشتن چربی پهلو و عمل لیفت سینه و بازو و تزریق ژل تو اندام و بوتاکس و پروتز لب و چاله چونه، و زاویه دار کردن فک و لنز توی چشم و رنگ مو و هزاران بدبختی و عذاب در قالب مدرنیته یا همون جاهلیت ثانی سر جنس ریحانه و لطیف زن میارن که چرخ ابر کمپانی های کپیتالیسم بچرخه ! و یا زن رو به نیروی کار ارزان،منشی یا کارگر برای کاهش هزینه تبدیل کنه بعد زن رو در یک رقابت ناتمام با همجنس خودش برای ظاهری بهتر داشتن قرار میدن که در آن احدی برنده نیست ! وقتی که باید صرف تعالی و سیر به سمت ملکوت بشه،زنی که میتونه مادری بشه که محسن حججی بپروره ! در تلقی غیر دینی وحید خزائی تربیت میکنه ! بعد چشم که باز میکنی میبینی چهره زن امروز با انجام تمام این کارهای حقنه شده غرب،از حالت عادی عاطفی خود به یک عروسک زشت مصنوعی و بدون عاطفه که صرفاً با فیزیک خود معرفی میشه شناخته شده ! یعنی با زدن حجاب، چنان بلایی به سر زن آوردن که زن امروز نیازمند یک منجیه ! این میشه که پولساز ترین سلبریتی‌های غرب مثل لیدی گاگا رو فرش قرمز با کت مردونه بیگ سایز میاد که بگه من آلت دست نیستم ! هشتگ های جهانی در نفی تجاوز راه میوفته در کره کمپین های نابودی لوازم آرایش،تظاهرات حقوق زنان رخ میده،مردم پلاکارد بالای سر خودشون میگیرن که life porn بیایید در مهندسی معکوس فرهنگی اینو بگید که زن در حجاب ناخودآگاه به تمام پیرامون اینو القا میکنه که من ارزشمندم،و مستحق احترام ! بعد زنه تو برنامه مذهبی قبل از اذان، 70سالشه فقط نوک دماغش بیرونه،از حضرت زهرا خرج میکنه که حضرت به حجاب اهمیت میداد ! یا حضرت زینب تو گودی قتلگاه هم حجاب شو نگه داشت ! چرا مثل آب خوردن از ائمه خرج میکنید؟ چرا بی دلیل تا قتلگاه میری نادون؟ بیا بگو دختر من این کره،اون هالیوود این دختره که رفت سیرجان،این مردا که از حقوق تو میگن زر میزنن،اینا تو رو کالا میبینن،برهنه و دم دست میخوانت ! column1: हमेशा ही अपने बयानों के चलते चर्चा में रहने वाली एक्ट्रेस कल्कि कोचलिन
column2: इस बार उन्होंने लड़की की वर्जिनिटी को लेकर बयान दिया है। हाल ही में उन्होंने  साल के अंत में पूरे साल में होने वाले मुद्दों के लेकर एक आर्टिकल लिखा। इस आर्टिकल में उन्होंने कई सारी बातों का जिक्र किया। कल्कि लिखती हैं कि भारतीयों को यौन शोषण के बारे में बातचीत को सामान्य बनाने और पुरुषों और महिलाओं को यौन रूप से सशक्त बनाने की आवश्यकता है। इसके साथ ही उन्होंने अपने आर्टिकल में #metoo के बारे में भी लिखा। उन्होंने कहा कि महिलाओं में सेक्स जागरूकता बढ़ाने की जरुरत है। #delhi #newdelhi #mumbai #kareena

column2: इस बार उन्होंने लड़की की वर्जिनिटी को लेकर बयान दिया है। हाल ही में उन्होंने  साल के अंत में पूरे साल में होने वाले मुद्दों के लेकर एक आर्टिकल लिखा। इस आर्टिकल में उन्होंने कई सारी बातों का जिक्र किया। कल्कि लिखती हैं कि भारतीयों को यौन शोषण के बारे में बातचीत को सामान्य बनाने और पुरुषों और महिलाओं को यौन रूप से सशक्त बनाने की आवश्यकता है। इसके साथ ही उन्होंने अपने आर्टिकल में #metoo के बारे में भी लिखा। उन्होंने कहा कि महिलाओं में सेक्स जागरूकता बढ़ाने की जरुरत है। #delhi #newdelhi #mumbai #kareena

i've shivers writing this down. its eerily silent and the ticking of clock doesn't help. i've never mustered the courage to speak this out
column2: not even now. speaking this as an anon is what feels a bit better. and i don't know if i can type this out any sooner am i just stalling. alright lets do it. i was a kid but i still remember it to even this day like it just happened yesterday. my heart is already thudding wild. i was asleep when i woke up to someone kissing me on the lips. i was confused.

column1: he thought i was still asleep so he took me in his arms
column2: and while pacing around the room
column3: began kissing me on the lips. i was awake. i remember how it felt. even now. i don't remember what happened next. at this point i stopped pretending i was asleep. he took me in a room. a very dimly lit room. i was wearing an outfit that didn't cover my hands. and he began kissing me up till my arm. all the way. up and down. and that's not the worst part. i was 4-5 years of age
column4: and im not sure if i knew it was wrong. i giggled. and asked him to kiss my hand. he smiled at me. and began kissing again. i don't remember what happened next. he came a few days later again. he asked me to get him a glass of water. that day i remembered that i hated him. and as a 5 year old the most i could do to get back at him was through something silly
column5: but felt angry at that age. so i mixed sevenup with the water. and gave it to him. he said that the water tasted funny. i said that's what we drink at home here. i felt proud of myself.

column1: it's been more than 10 years since then and i haven't told my parents. he still comes around
column2: but rarely. and by the way he talks to me doesn't feel like he remembers what he did to me.
the more it haunts me. the more i realize that this was something serious. the more it traumatises me as i grow older.

column1: this isn't just it. this was the very first incident from many of other sexual harassment cases with me.
some day i'll be strong enough to let it not haunt me. not today

column1: 84776;instagram;2019-01-08 19:01:05;FALSE;"if you caught the story i posted last night
column2: you’d see how i talked about some major red flags i noticed in my relationship with my abuser. he’d brag about illegal activities he’d done. hearing those definitely scared me. what was he capable of doing to me if i left him? that question definitely kept me around for longer than i care to admit.

column1: but i did end up leaving him
column2: and that “spark” that finally triggered my decision to move is important to talk about too.

my abuser had come home (probably drunk) and told me that he remembered me as a stronger woman before we had started dating. “what happened to that girl?” he had said. i felt weak and ashamed. but that moment triggered something inside me. i wasn’t weak. i had been putting up with his bull for almost 2 years
column3: and that was making me strong. and i think he sensed that. even though it took me another two months to leave him after he said that
column4: that day was my spark. that was the day i decided to leave him.

column1: what was your spark? what caused you to leave your abuser? what happened that helped you realize you were in an abusive relationship?
nobody gets away with calling me weak. i’m pretty proud of what my spark is 🔥❤️ #weareher

column1: how good intentions and bad ideas are setting up a generation for failure

first amendment expert greg lukianoff and social psychologist jonathan haidt show how the new problems on campus have their origins in three terrible ideas that have become increasingly woven into american childhood and education: what doesn’t kill you makes you weaker; always trust your feelings; and life is a battle between good people and evil people. these three great untruths contradict basic psychological principles about well-being and ancient wisdom from many cultures.  embracing these untruths—and the resulting culture of safetyism—interferes with young people’s social
column3: and intellectual development. it makes it harder for them to become autonomous adults who are able to navigate the bumpy road of life.

column5: to implicit bias and diversity compliance training that sees racism in every interaction

column2: i vowed to turn my passion into a profession! as a student entering college from a low-income background
column3: i wanted to continue my work with @periodmovement with as much commitment as i had in high school when i founded the organization at age 16. it took a while
column4: and it was a challenge – but together
column5: our team pushed period to keep growing
column7: and we built a pool of resources to be able to compensate our core team members
column8: and eventually hire our first full-time staff in the summer of 2017.

column1: my determination now continues to encourage other young people to turn their passion into a profession
column2: and i am excited to travel more over the next few months to speak to young activists around the country
column4: and prepare to return to harvard in the fall.

column2: where we raised over $200k to build our capacity
column3: and hopefully bring on some new team members! .

column1: 84917;instagram;2019-01-08 16:28:24;FALSE;"من با#حجاب کاری ندارم،آقا اگر حجاب نباشه چی میشه؟

زنی که بهش گفتن حجاب و بزار کنار،یعنی اندام تو نشون بده بدون تعارف،حالا ابتدای مسیر بی انتهای ظاهرگرایی و#اصالت_لذت افتاده،حالا که افتاد تو دام#لیبرالیسم_فرهنگی که معتقد به این است که در عالم تمام پدیده ها کالا!و قابل خرید و فروش هستند،زن به مثابه کالا تلقی میشه!
کالایی که مانند اپل و پاناسونیک و تسلا باید در بالاترین کیفیت به مرد عرضه بشه!

حالا کمپانی های عظیم مد،آرایش،جراحی های افسارگسیخته،از نوک ناخن پا،با انواع و اقسام کاشت های ناخن تا زیورآلات مچ پا تا آرایش ساق پا کشیدگی پوست و خالکوبی،برداشتن چربی پهلو،عمل لیفت سینه و بازو،تزریق ژل تو اندام و بوتاکس و پروتز لب و چاله چونه، زاویه دار کردن فک و لنز توی چشم و رنگ مو،اکستنشن و هزاران بدبختی و عذاب در قالب#مدرنیته یا همون جاهلیت ثانی سر جنس ریحانه و لطیف زن میارن که چرخ ابر کمپانی های کپیتالیسم بچرخه!
و یا زن رو به نیروی کار ارزان،منشی یا کارگر برای کاهش هزینه تبدیل کنه
بعد زن رو در یک رقابت ناتمام با همجنس خودش برای ظاهری بهتر داشتن قرار میدن که در آن احدی برنده نیست!
وقتی که باید صرف تعالی و سیر به سمت ملکوت بشه،زنی که میتونه مادری بشه که محسن حججی  بپروره!
در تلقی غیر دینی وحید خزائی تربیت میکنه!
بعد چشم که باز میکنی میبینی چهره زن امروز با انجام تمام این کارهای حقنه شده غرب،از حالت عادی عاطفی خود به یک عروسک زشت مصنوعی و بدون عاطفه که صرفاً با فیزیک خود معرفی میشه شناخته شده!
یعنی با زدن حجاب، چنان بلایی به سر زن آوردن که زن امروز نیازمند یک منجیه!
این میشه که پولساز ترین سلبریتی‌های غرب مثل لیدی گاگا رو فرش قرمز با کت مردونه بیگ سایز میاد که بگه من آلت دست نیستم!
هشتگ های جهانی#metoo در نفی تجاوز راه میوفته
در کره کمپین های نابودی لوازم آرایش،تظاهرات حقوق زنان رخ میده،مردم پلاکارد بالای سر خودشون میگیرن کهmy life is not your porn
بیایید در مهندسی معکوس فرهنگی و جدال احسن اینو بگید که زن در حجاب ناخودآگاه به تمام پیرامون اینو القا میکنه که من ارزشمندم،و مستحق احترام!
بعد زنه تو برنامه مذهبی قبل از اذان، 70سالشه فقط نوک دماغش بیرونه،از حضرت زهرا خرج میکنه که حضرت به حجاب اهمیت میداد!
حضرت زینب تو گودی قتلگاه هم حجاب شو نگه داشت!
چرا راحت از ائمه خرج میکنید؟
چرا بی دلیل تا قتلگاه میری نادون؟
بیا بگو دختر من این کره،اون هالیوود این دختره که رفت سیرجان،این مردا که از حقوق تو میگن زر میزنن،اینا تو رو کالا میبینن،برهنه و دم دست میخوانت!

column1: 84923;instagram;2019-01-08 16:30:34;FALSE;"what's your favourite book on #feminism? i am looking for ideas 🤓

column2: the goal was no longer to reform the political system to include women
column4: to challenge the idea that inclusion in this system necessarily made women “free.” page after page
column5: you cannot but notice how the second sex legacy still resonates now

column3: fearlessly. because just like compassion and empathy
column4: peace cannot be argued. peace cannot be ""wrong"" nor can one ""fight"" for peace. it's a daily practice that subverts the paradigm of right and wrong completely.

column1: 84986;instagram;2019-01-08 15:31:07;FALSE;what does word “boundaries” mean to you? i think it’s something that on many occasions is not spoken about enough until the situation becomes so toxic that it explodes as it was in case with #metoo and #timeisup movement. obviously it’s pronounced more in certain countries and industries but since we all inhabit the same planet
column2: i think it’s important to talk about it even if we are not affected directly. plus there are so many smaller scale ways in which our boundaries can be violated daily. by “our” i mean both men and women
column3: however the conditioning is very different when it comes to how we deal with it. men are allowed to get angry
column4: women not so much. we are expected to be “nice” at all times - even when the situation calls for not a nice response. this double standard is a bit like - women are allowed to be vulnerable and cry
column5: men not. both of those scenarios produce the same result - suppressed emotions. which can lead to possible health problems later on. this is not a call to get angry every time someone is rude to you but rather to learn to confront/stand up for yourself in a healthy way when it’s needed. something i avoided at all costs in the past as it felt much safer to just withdraw and ignore/avoid the person. there is however no growth in this approach and 2018 was big on boundary setting  lessons. #boundaries #selfawareness #growth #yinyang #takeyourpowerback #empowerment #comfortzone #resolutions #photooftheday #instalike #instagood #foodforthought 🌚🌝;;en;#metoo

column1: okay so this might be crazy to post my ovulation stick on social media but being the vulnerability queen what do y’all expect? 😂⁣
in preparation to start trying to conceive next month after danny’s surgery this month
column2: i started being proactive. i started two weeks ago charting my temperature every morning and 3 days ago started taking ovulation tests to see when i start ovulating in my cycle etc. i’ve been noticing ovulation for a few months now which in the past i never had signs of ovulation. ⁣

column1: yesterday was a no/low ovulation day with just an empty circle and this morning i teared up after seeing this cute smiley face saying i was ovulating. 😊⁣

i still remember being 17 and scared in that awful hospital gown the first of many times i heard i probably couldn’t have biological kids as they rambled off the list of things wrong with me and surgeries to come...things i won’t even repeat because i refuse to give life to them. ⁣
but what i remember more is 12 years later at 29 meeting a young stud (almost 5 years my junior) that proved all the doctor’s wrong by getting me pregnant. 😂 we jokingly call d
though i had a rough pregnancy
column2: labor and delivery was a breeze
column3: but i still thought i was one and done. we had our miracle baby and i never wanted to go through that awful pregnancy or postpartum anxiety again. never. ⁣

column2: because after a ton of healing
column6: we are here on this journey and more excited than ever to have another baby. and i feel in my heart we will be pregnant this year. i refuse to believe anything or anyone that tries to say different. ⁣

column1: the mind is a powerful tool and this smiley face gives me hope in itself. never give up because someone else tells you it’s not possible. one day in the near future this will be a positive pregnancy test. i believe it. 💗🙏🏻✨⁣
